Let $\alpha$ and $\beta$ be angles such that
\[\frac{\cos \alpha}{\cos \beta} + \frac{\sin \alpha}{\sin \beta} = -1.\]Find all possible values of
\[\frac{\cos^3 \beta}{\cos \alpha} + \frac{\sin^3 \beta}{\sin \alpha}.\]Enter all possible values, separated by commas.
inference:
Solution:
We have
\begin{align*}
\frac{\cos \alpha}{\cos \beta} + \frac{\sin \alpha}{\sin \beta} &= -1\\
\Rightarrow\qquad \frac{\cos \alpha \sin \beta + \sin \alpha \cos \beta}{\cos \beta \sin \beta} &= -1\\
\Rightarrow\qquad \cos \alpha \sin \beta + \sin \alpha \cos \beta &= -\cos \beta \sin \beta\\
\Rightarrow\qquad \sin (\alpha + \beta) &= -\cos \beta \sin \beta\\
\Rightarrow\qquad \sin (\alpha + \beta) &= -\frac{1}{2} \sin 2\beta\\
\Rightarrow\qquad \alpha + \beta &= \pi - 2\beta + 2n\pi\\
\Rightarrow\qquad \alpha &= \pi - 3\beta + 2n\pi.
\end{align*}Therefore,
\begin{align*}
\frac{\cos^3 \beta}{\cos \alpha} + \frac{\sin^3 \beta}{\sin \alpha} &= \frac{\cos^3 \beta}{\cos (\pi - 3\beta + 2n\pi)} + \frac{\sin^3 \beta}{\sin (\pi - 3\beta + 2n\pi)}\\
&= \frac{\cos^3 \beta}{-\cos (3\beta - 2n\pi)} + \frac{\sin^3 \beta}{-\sin (3\beta - 2n\pi)}\\
&= \frac{\cos^3 \beta}{-\cos (3\beta - 2n\pi)} + \frac{\sin^3 \beta}{-\sin (3\beta - 2n\pi)}\\
&= \frac{\cos^3 \beta}{\cos (3\beta - 2n\pi)} + \frac{\sin^3 \beta}{\sin (3\beta - 2n\pi)}\\
&= \frac{\cos^3 \beta}{\cos 3\beta \cos 2n\pi + \sin 3\beta \sin 2n\pi} + \frac{\sin^3 \beta}{\sin 3\beta \cos 2n\pi - \cos 3\beta \sin 2n\pi}\\
&= \frac{\cos^3 \beta}{\cos 3\beta} + \frac{\sin^3 \beta}{\sin 3\beta}\\
&= \cos^2 \beta + \sin^2 \beta\\
&= \boxed{1}.
\end{align*}
Final Answer: $\boxed{1}.$ I hope it is correct.
ground_truth:
Let $k = \frac{\cos \alpha}{\cos \beta}.$  Then $\frac{\sin \alpha}{\sin \beta} = -k - 1,$ so $\cos \alpha = k \cos \beta$ and $\sin \alpha = -(k + 1) \sin \beta.$  Substituting into $\cos^2 \alpha + \sin^2 \alpha = 1,$ we get
\[k^2 \cos^2 \beta + (k + 1)^2 \sin^2 \beta = 1.\]Then $k^2 \cos^2 \beta + (k + 1)^2 (1 - \cos^2 \beta) = 1,$ which leads to
\[\cos^2 \beta = \frac{k^2 + 2k}{2k + 1}.\]Therefore,
\[\sin^2 \beta = 1 - \cos^2 \beta = \frac{1 - k^2}{2k + 1}.\]Hence,
\begin{align*}
\frac{\cos^3 \beta}{\cos \alpha} + \frac{\sin^3 \beta}{\sin \alpha} &= \cos^2 \beta \cdot \frac{\cos \beta}{\cos \alpha} + \sin^2 \beta \cdot \frac{\sin \beta}{\sin \alpha} \\
&= \frac{k^2 + 2k}{2k + 1} \cdot \frac{1}{k} + \frac{1 - k^2}{2k + 1} \cdot \frac{1}{-k - 1} \\
&= \frac{k + 2}{2k + 1} + \frac{k - 1}{2k + 1} \\
&= \frac{2k + 1}{2k + 1} = \boxed{1}.
\end{align*}
